## Example 1 ÔÇö Solve and Graph One-Variable Inequality

Solve $3x - 7 > 8$ and graph the solution on a number line.

### Step 1: Add 7 to Both Sides

$$3x > 15$$

### Step 2: Divide by 3

$$x > 5$$

### Step 3: Graph

On a number line, place an **open circle** at 5 (5 is not included) and shade to the right.

```
ÔćÉÔÇöÔÇöÔÇöÔŚő================Ôćĺ
    5
```

### Step 4: Verify

Test $x = 6$: $3(6) - 7 = 18 - 7 = 11 > 8$ Ôťô

Test $x = 5$: $3(5) - 7 = 15 - 7 = 8 \not> 8$ ÔťŚ (5 is not in the solution set)

Ôťů Answer: $x > 5$. Open circle at 5, shade right.

