## Example 3 ÔÇö Compound Inequality (AND)

Solve $-3 < 2x + 1 \leq 7$.

### Step 1: Subtract 1 from All Three Parts

$$-4 < 2x \leq 6$$

### Step 2: Divide All Parts by 2

$$-2 < x \leq 3$$

### Step 3: Graph

Open circle at $-2$ (not included), closed circle at 3 (included), shade between.

```
ÔćÉÔÇöÔÇöÔÇöÔÇöÔÇöÔÇöÔŚő=============ÔŚĆÔÇöÔÇöÔÇöÔÇöÔćĺ
      -2              3
```

### Step 4: Verify

Test $x = 0$: $-3 < 2(0) + 1 = 1 \leq 7$ Ôťô

Test $x = -2$: $2(-2) + 1 = -3 \not> -3$ ÔťŚ (not in solution)

Test $x = 3$: $2(3) + 1 = 7 \leq 7$ Ôťô (included)

Ôťů Answer: $-2 < x \leq 3$.

